      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1aaf3f806462ebd0",
      "text": "Like a data carrier, this represents the real good and frees it from its imponderables. A still unregulated monetary community that has raised a metal to the status of money – a so-called commodity money – is burdened with weight and [[Authenticity]] checks and possibly procurement problems. If this central office acquires a mint, the monetary community is freed from these burdens by having metal coins stamped and weighed in advance and can thus reduce its transaction costs."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "91a1c9072038bfdb",
      "text": "The [[Coin]] or mint is thus regarded as the original form of the [[Central Bank]]. For the original monetary community, the central bank is primary because its money economizes indirect exchange, while banks come into play only secondarily in the case of credit for the settlement of intertemporal exchange and then constitute a subsidiary monetary community which, together with the original one, forms the hybrid monetary community of the exchange economy with money use."
